The '''Commission on Accreditation for Health Informatics and Information Management Education''' ('''CAHIIM''') is the accrediting organization for degree-granting programs in [[health informatics]] and [[health information management]].<ref>The Ohio State University. [http://amp.osu.edu/hims/1358.cfm Health Information Management & Systems: About The Program] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100129070059/http://amp.osu.edu/HIMS/1358.cfm |date=2010-01-29 }}. Retrieved 1/8/2010.</ref> Its Board of Commissions is made up of 12 volunteers, 8 of which are elected by the general membership of CAHIIM's sponsor, [[American Health Information Management Association]] (AHIMA).<ref>International Network for Quality Assurance Agencies in Higher Education. [http://www.inqaahe.org/members/member-detail.php?membertype=o&memberID=577 Member profile for Commission on Accreditation for Health Informatics and Information Management Education (CAHIIM)]. Retrieved 1/8/2010.</ref> CAHIIM is recognized by CHEA as an organization that accredits associate and baccalaureate degree programs in health information management and master's degree programs in health informatics and health information management professions in the United States and Puerto Rico.
